tip.text: Adorable Portuguese bakery with the most authentic pastel de nata in Montreal reminding me of the ones I have in Portugal.
Not sure how this place doesn't have a 10 rating. Service is exceptional. Food is delicious. And the ambiance makes it a must see on a stay in Montreal.
A wonderful sleek oasis in the canggu hustle and bustle. I felt like I was transported to a cool cafe in tribeca with the amazing mix of beautiful wood furniture and modern fixtures.
The best omakase I've ever had. An amazing two hour experience with the head chef, amazing service.... What an experience.
Great live jazz music on Thursdays and $5 sangria! The perfect place for a quick bite and to relax.
The best matcha latte in NYC.
Avocado toast is to die for
Love the banana Mille if you are looking to switch it up or don't like creme too much.
Try one of each!

formattedAddress: #B2-47/48 The Shoppes @ Marina Bay Sands (10 Bayfront Ave)

tip.text: The temple and adjacent rows and rows of markets are the perfect intersection between peace and chaos.

formattedAddress: 211 New Bridge Rd. (opp People's Park Complex)

tip.text: Always massive crowds but adds to the experience.
I was worried the Singaporean boutique wouldn't capture the amazing texture and flavor of the NYC stores but was I wrong; Frothy, light and delicious with a lovely shop situated on the Marina.
Yummy warm muffins that cost just a donation to the tip jar. Free wifi, a nice alternative to an ever busy group therapy down the road.
Lovely atmosphere and amazing tapas. Definitely on the pricier side for the portions. A lovely place for a date.
Delicious toasted almond latte. Try to avoid the Sunday morning brunch rush.

formattedAddress: 45 Ann Siang Hill #02-02 (Ann Siang Hill Park)

tip.text: Head all the way upstairs for the attic bar and lounge! Delicious cakes that had my mouth watering the second I saw them in the display. Also great staff and service.

formattedAddress: 45 Ann Siang Hill #02-02 (Ann Siang Hill Park)

tip.text: Yummy smoothies and free wifi, great afternoon work spot with fun energetic Kpop blasting in the background. Good vibes.
Try the mushroom truffle soup! So rich and creamy and topped with a lovely whipped fizzy cream!
Coconut curry soup and beef rendeng the bomb diggity.

W 4th St (btwn MacDougal St & University Pl)

tip.text: Pricey drinks are a fair exchange for the best view of Manhattan right in Manhattan.
That. View.

formattedAddress: 96 Saint Marks Pl (btwn 1st Ave & Avenue A)

tip.text: The quintessential cool east village spot with a cozy setup and an amazing selection of rice wine.
The view is unbeatable here. Very posh Brooklyn crowd that gave me the quintessential Willysburg experience.
Go for the rooftop during lunch time as this place gets packed once the work day lets out. Sangria and margaritas are top notch.
